author: Ben Leubsdorf
title: U.S. Industrial Production Rose 1.1% in February
text:
WASHINGTON—Industrial output jumped in February as American factories ramped up production, signaling healthy momentum in a key sector of the U.S. economy.
Industrial production—a measure of total output at U.S. factories, mines and utilities—increased a seasonally adjusted 1.1% in February from the prior month, the Federal Reserve said Friday. Economists surveyed by The Wall Street Journal had expected a more modest 0.4% gain.
